Name: ?? description wanted, apply here ??
Fill Value: Please ensure that the fill_value is NOT a valid value for the parameter. For example, 0 is typically a very poor fill_value since it is usually valid (i.e. for temp, lat, lon, pressure, salinity, etc)
Ion Name: The expected display name for R2.1 and beyond. Will be a required field in R2.1 and beyond. May not be used in 2.0
Standard name: The CF standard name for this parameter: http://cf-pcmdi.llnl.gov/documents/cf-standard-names/standard-name-table/20/cf-standard-name-table.html
Long Name: OOI documentation long name for L0
OOI Short Name: OOI documentation short name (abbreviation) for L0

Name: conductivity
Description: The OOI Level 1 Conductivity data product is computed by converting raw hexadecimal conductivity data from the conductivity, temperature and depth (CTD) family of instruments into Siemens/meter.

Name: pressure
Description: The OOI Level 1 Pressure (Depth) core data product is computed by converting raw hexadecimal pressure data from the conductivity, temperature and depth (CTD) family of instruments into decibars.

Name: salinity
Description: The OOI Level 2 Salinity core data product is computed using the TEOS-10 equations for practical salinity with data from the conductivity, temperature, and depth (CTD) family of instruments.

Name: density
Description: The OOI Level 2 Density core data product is computed using the TEOS-10 equations with data from the conductivity, temperature and depth (CTD) family of instruments.

Name: temp
Description: The OOI Level 1 Pressure (Depth) core data product is computed by converting raw hexadecimal pressure data from the conductivity, temperature and depth (CTD) family of instruments into decibars.

Name: time
Description: Time in seconds since 1970-01-01

Name: port_timestamp
Description: Port timestamp in seconds since 1970-01-01

Name: driver_timestamp
Description: Driver timestamp in seconds since 1970-01-01

Name: internal_timestamp
Description: Internal timestamp in seconds since 1970-01-01

Name: pressure_temp
Description: The OOI Level 1 Pressure (Depth) core data product is computed by converting raw hexadecimal pressure data from the conductivity, temperature and depth (CTD) family of instruments into decibars.

Name: CONDWAT_GLBLRNG_QC
Description: The OOI Global Range quality control algorithm generates a QC flag for the input data point indicating whether it falls within a given range.

Name: CONDWAT_LOCLRNG_QC
Description: The local range test is a QC test that reports whether input data points fall within given ranges

Name: CONDWAT_SPKETST_QC
Description: The OOI Spike Test quality control algorithm generates a flag for individual data values that deviate significantly from surrounding data values.

Name: CONDWAT_STUCKVL_QC
Description: The OOI Stuck Value Test quality control algorithm generates a flag for repeated occurrence of one value in a time series.

Name: CONDWAT_SPTL_GRADTST_QC
Description: The OOI Gradient Test quality control algorithm generates QC flags indicating whether changes between successive data points in space fall within a given range.

Name: CONDWAT_TMPL_GRADTST_QC
Description: The OOI Gradient Test quality control algorithm generates QC flags indicating whether changes between successive data points in time fall within a given range.
